  "Magical Jewelry": {
    "index": "0",
    "category": "artifice",
    "tier": 1,
    "sections": [
      {
        "type": "title",
        "value": "Magical Jewelry"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "",
        "json": [
          {
            "text": "Magical jewelry relies on a "
          },
          {
            "text": "special jewel",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": " that reacts with the metal the piece is made out of. Jewels have different effects depending on if they're set into "
          },
          {
            "text": "gold",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": " or into "
          },
          {
            "text": "silver",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": ".\n\n"
          },
          {
            "text": "Ancient jewelry",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": " with magical properties can occasionally be found in the old "
          },
          {
            "text": "treasure chests",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": " left across the world by a bygone era. These pieces can be worn as-is for a small magical boost, but they can be "
          },
          {
            "text": "enhanced using modern artifice techniques",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": ".\n\nThe simplest improvement requires setting a jewel in a new piece. A suitable setting can be created by plating a Mundane Amulet, Bracelet, or Ring with a block of an appropriate metal on a Runic Anvil.\n\nJewels can be "
          },
          {
            "text": "retrieved",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": " from a piece of Ancient jewelry by Construct crushing. Unset jewels can also be found by searching "
          },
          {
            "text": "suspicious sand or gravel",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": " in "
          },
          {
            "text": "certain structures",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": ". The Wandering Wizard sells thaumaturgic links to these structures (search her wares for structures that begin with \""
          },
          {
            "text": "arcado",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": "\").\n\nAs you increase in Tier, "
          },
          {
            "text": "new recipes",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": " to enhance your magical jewelry will appear in this entry. Magical Jewelry can be enhanced up to "
          },
          {
            "text": "Grade 3",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": ".\n\nIf "
          },
          {
            "text": "MagiChem",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": " is installed then magical jewelry can be enhanced up to "
          },
          {
            "text": "Grade 5",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": " and can be made out of "
          },
          {
            "text": "electrum",
            "color": "dark_purple"
          },
          {
            "text": " to make pieces that grant a mix of the jewel's Gold and Silver effects."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
